post_text:
New Waverly High School will be hosting a Hurricane Laura Donation Drive with the New Waverly FFA. The following items that we are looking for include...

Cleaning Supplies (bleach, Clorox, soap, baby wipes, Clorox wipes, Lysol)
Hygiene Products
Tarps
Water, Gatorade, Powerade
Dog/Cat food
Toiletries
Paper Products (paper towels, toilet paper)
Mops, Brooms, Buckets, Dust pans, Trash bags
Work gloves
Face masks
Non-Perishable foods that do not need to be heated
Dish Soap
Mosquito repellent
Ice chest

Mr. Wilson will be staying at the high school everyday until 6pm to receive items at the AG SHOP. We will be collecting throughout the month of September and we will be taking our first load on Saturday, September 5th, 2020.

If you have any questions please contact Mr. Wilson at 936-827-4332 or at cwilson@new-waverly.k12.tx.us

post_text:
⚡️DAY EIGHT OF OUR 2020-2021 NW FFA OFFICER SPOTLIGHT⚡️
.

Hey y’all! I am currently serving as your 2020-2021 New Waverly FFA President. I am also a New Waverly High School Varsity Cheerleader. This will be my fourth year in FFA, my tenth year as an involved 4-H member and my tenth year to show market steers. In the past three years as an FFA member I have participated in radio broadcasting, public relations, job interview and I advanced to state with my record book for the past three years. Agriculture has always been so close to my heart and I love to share my passion for it with everyone around me. FFA has completely changed me as a person; if you knew me as a freshman you would know how shy I was, in the past three years I have broken out of my shell and become a confident leader and example to my peers. I am so excited for the year ahead with my officer team that has quickly become a small family to me. Never be afraid to reach out to me if you need anything or just need to see a smiling face!

Love,
Kendyll Williams🤍

post_text:
⚡️DAY SEVEN OF OUR 2020-2021 NW FFA OFFICER SPOTLIGHT⚡️
.
Howdy 🤠!!! I'm Brady Wilson From the New Waverly FFA chapter, and I am honored to serve as your 2020-2021 Vice President, as well as a Sam Houston District 3rd Vice President. Growing up in Ag and with 2 parents who are now my Ag teachers, this has been a dream of mine for years. Last year I served as the New Waverly FFA Secretary. I participate in many district, area and state FFA activities. I show poultry at every Major Livestock show in Texas and have been very fortunate to have won Grand Champion at the State Fair and San Antonio Livestock show. There are only 4 things I love dearly in my heart and that's poultry, traveling, aviation, and this great FFA organization. I'm beyond excited to serve as the Vice President this year and can't wait for our adventures in this upcoming year. If you ever need anything just give me buzz and I will be glad to help.
💙💛🐔😃😁🤪

post_text: New Waverly and our amazing FFA chapter is located directly between Huntsville and Conroe,Texas on I-45. The heart of our chapter is our “small town” members that love to show cattle, poultry, pigs, sheep, and goats. Our members are skilled in Ag mechanics, greenhouse productions, Public speaking and leadership events. It is our active and service oriented chapter that makes us a successful FFA Chapter in the great state of TEXAS !!!

shared_text:
Texas Farm Credit
May 7 at 3:14 PM ·

Congratulations to our six scholarship winners! Out of hundreds of applications, these outstanding students rose to the top!

Each winner will receive a $2,000 scholarship as well as a $500 donation to their FFA or 4H club.

Let’s hear it for the following winners who will all be attending Texas A&M University in the fall!

• Baylee Glaze from Tioga High School & Tioga FFA
• Haley Jouett from Kaufman ISD High School & Kaufman TX FFA
• Katelyn Klawinsky from New Waverly ISD High School & New Waverly FFA
• Braylee Schomburg from Brenham ISD High School & Sandy Hill 4-H Club
• Matthew Marquez from Detroit High School & Detroit FFA
• Kate McNeill from Pleasanton High School & Atascosa County 4-H HORSE Club/Atascosa Club of Equine Enthusiasts

Read more about each student here: https://bit.ly/3duPR8v

#TFCAgStudents Rock!!! 💚

post_text: New Waverly FFA is looking for people to sponsor trailers for our build off team this year. These trailers are 77” wide, 10 feet in length, and come with a ramp on the rear. Our team competes with other schools across the state building these trailers in 7 hours or less using only the tools they can fit in a truck. We have done very well the last couple years in these contests. If you are interested in a trailer, please contact Mr. Wilson at the high school for details.

post_text: Spent the day helping out people affected by the flooding. We worked with students from Walker High School FFA from Baton Rouge, Louisiana. We were able to help the community of Nome, Texas get a church back in order, and clean up some things around town. The trailer load is what we came home with to send to other areas that need help. These items were no longer needed in the community, so we brought them back to see if we can redistribute to those in need! Great day helping others!

We were able to help the community of Nome, Texas get a church back in order, and clean up some things around town. The trailer load is what we came home with to send to other areas that need help. These items were no longer needed in the community, so we brought them back to see if we can redistribute to those in need! Great day helping others!

Notes for the week for NWFFA:
Tomorrow (Sunday) is a fair work day from 2-4 pm. Please Make sure your child has their 5 work hours or else they do not show or participate in the fair.

Monday & Wednesday I need to schedule a final chicken culling time for all broiler exhibiters. I would like to have this final cull completed by Friday night but at the latest Sunday morning early.

Tuesday I will be in EOC testing all day (5hours). I am giving the test so please do not send me text or emails about the fair and expect a quick response or any reply at all - Please wait if possible till Wednesday.

Please remember that my father-law is very ill and our plans for assisting you before the fair my change at the last minute. Please have a back plan if needed and please keep our family in your prayers. We really appreciate all your support and prayers to this point.

post_text: We are leaving Monday morning for Dallas for the Texas FFA Convention with 8 kiddos. I pray today for our safety but are determined to not take the joy from these kids who have worked so hard and deserve this trip. It's more than just attending. We have rodeo contestants, two science fair entries, Lone Star Degree recipients, 3 Star Degree recipients. These kids will attend a leadership workshop, be voting delegates, be motivated by speakers and get more from this one week than I can teach them in a semester. So I will pack my stuff and educate my kids on safety, have a plan, stay by their side, and do all I can to not take away their joy. So Dallas get ready- there's 10,000+ FFA members coming!

Please help spread the word and keep everyone informed!!
